cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IT

This paper discusses the modification of inference rules in probabilistic networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on functional dependencies suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT) and the use of deterministic variables may relate to the study of discrete structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of qualitative synergy may indicate a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SI).
